  "local_port": 43198,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have insomnia and it seems I've developed tolerance to trazodone. I won't see my doctor for 3 weeks. What do I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you're struggling with insomnia. Dealing with sleep issues and medication tolerance can be very frustrating. Here are some steps you can take while waiting to see your doctor:\n\n### 1. **Consult Your Doctor (If Possible)**\n   - Even if your appointment is in 3 weeks, consider reaching out to your doctor\u2019s office to inform them about your situation. They may provide guidance over the phone or adjust your appointment.\n   - If your doctor is unavailable, ask if you can speak with a nurse or physician assistant.\n\n### 2. **Avoid Increasing Dosage on Your Own**\n   - Do not increase your trazodone dosage without medical supervision, as this can lead to side effects or further tolerance.\n\n### 3. **Practice Good Sleep Hygiene**\n   - **Consistent Schedule:** Go to bed and wake up at the same time every day, even on weekends.\n   - **Sleep Environment:** Make your bedroom dark, quiet, and cool. Avoid screens (TV, phone, etc.) at least an hour before bed.\n   - **Relaxation Techniques:** Try deep breathing, meditation, or progressive muscle relaxation to calm your mind before bed.\n   - **Limit Stimulants:** Avoid caffeine, nicotine, and heavy meals close to bedtime.\n\n### 4. **Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Insomnia (CBT-I)**\n   - CBT-I is a highly effective treatment for insomnia that doesn\u2019t involve medication. Look for online resources or apps (e.g., Sleepio, CBT-I Coach) to help you get started.\n\n### 5. **Consider Over-the-Counter Options (with Caution)**\n   - **Melatonin:** A low dose (0.5\u20133 mg) taken 1\u20132 hours before bed may help regulate your sleep cycle. It\u2019s generally safe but works best for circadian rhythm issues.\n   - **Antihistamines:** Diphenhydramine (e.g., Benadryl) or doxylamine (e.g., Unisom) can induce drowsiness but should only be used short-term, as they can cause grogginess and tolerance.\n\n### 6. **Avoid Alcohol and Sedatives**\n   - These can disrupt sleep quality and worsen insomnia in the long run.\n\n### 7. **Stay Active**\n   - Regular exercise during the day can improve sleep, but avoid vigorous activity close to bedtime.\n\n### 8. **Track Your Sleep**\n   - Keep a sleep diary to monitor patterns and identify triggers for your insomnia. This can also help your doctor make adjustments to your treatment.\n\n### 9. **Stay Calm**\n   - Anxiety about not sleeping can worsen insomnia. Remind yourself that rest, even if not deep sleep, is still beneficial.\n\n### 10. **Consider a Pharmacist\u2019s Advice**\n   - Speak with a pharmacist about your trazodone tolerance. They may provide suggestions for non-prescription options or lifestyle changes.\n\n### When to Seek Immediate Help:\n   - If your insomnia is causing severe distress, excessive fatigue, or impacting your ability to function, consider seeking urgent care or contacting a mental health professional.\n\nIn the meantime, focus on healthy sleep habits and stress management. Let your doctor know about your tolerance issues at your next appointment so they can explore alternative treatments or adjustments to your current regimen.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
